700444f-a.text:
2556 Bainbridge Ave., east side, between East Fordham Road and
East 193rd Street, showing repair work in progress on the roof of the
Fordham Branch of the New York Public Library.
September 24, 1936.
Works Progress Administration.
Federal Art Project photo.
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.

700441f-a.title: Bronx: Bainbridge Avenue - Fordham Road (East)
700441f-a.text:
2556 Bainbridge Ave., east side, between East Fordham Road, and
East 193rd Street, showing W.P.A. workmen building an addition to the
rear of the Fordham Branch of the New York Public Library on Marion
Ave. After completion the library will extend from Bainbridge to Marion
Aves.
May 12, 1936.
Works Progress Administration.
Federal Art Project photo.
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.
